The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Oct. 6: Adding to Escorts?s woes in selling its hospital to Fortis Healthcare, the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) today cancelled the lease agreement of Escorts Heart Institute and Research Centre (EHIRC) alleging violation of certain conditions of the pact. In a notice served to EHIRC, the DDA said, ?The competent authority has decided to determine the lease deeds of EHRIC. Accordingly, you are directed to peacefully yield up the said land and building thereon to the lessor ? DDA.?

 Mumbai, Oct. 6: ITC Ltd has issued and allotted over 125.17 crore ordinary shares of Re 1 each as bonus shares. Following this, the paid up share capital of the company has increased to over Rs 375.51 crore, ITC has informed Bombay Stock Exchange.

 New Delhi, Oct. 6: In a major relief to exporters, the government is likely to exempt negative profits from the tax purview by amending the controversial provisions in the income tax laws by November. The amendment is likely to be carried out by way of issuing an ordinance.

 Calcutta, Oct. 6: Calcutta High Court has directed the jute commissioner to fix a price ceiling for raw jute.

 Mumbai, Oct. 6: Voltas Ltd today announced transfer of its 50 per cent stake in joint venture Sermo-PM India Ltd to France-based Sermo (SAS).




